  • Method Details

    • checkHandleExists

      public VolatileBlobApi.CheckHandleExistsAdapter checkHandleExists(String hrn, String layerId, String dataHandle, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Checks if a volatile blob exists for the requested data handle.

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/data/{dataHandle}

      Method: HEAD

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : String (OK - dataHandle exists)

      code 204 : (DataHandle exists but blob is empty)

      code 401 : AuthenticationMessage (Unauthorized)

      code 403 : AuthorizationMessage (Forbidden)

      code 404 : (Not Found - dataHandle doesn't exist)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The ID of the layer that the volatile blob belongs to.
      dataHandle - The data handle identifies a specific volatile blob so that you can get that blob's contents.
      billingTag - Billing Tag is an optional free-form tag which is used for grouping billing records together. If supplied, it must be between 4 - 16 characters, contain only alpha/numeric ASCII characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Grouping billing records by billing tag will be available in future releases.

    • deleteVolatileBlob

      public VolatileBlobApi.DeleteVolatileBlobAdapter deleteVolatileBlob(String hrn, String layerId, String dataHandle, Optional<String> xReplicate, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Deletes a volatile data blob from the underlying storage mechanism (volume).

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/data/{dataHandle}

      Method: DELETE

      Expected answers:

      code 204 : (Deleted - the data blob was successfully deleted.)

      code 401 : AuthorizationMessage (Unauthorized)

      code 403 : AuthorizationMessage (Forbidden)

      code 404 : (Not Found - data blob with the specified data handle does not exist)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The ID of the layer that the volatile data blob belongs to.
      dataHandle - The data handle (ID) represents an identifier for the volatile data blob which contents will be deleted.
      xReplicate - If set to true, it indicates the request is a replication call. It is not required for user to set it manually
      billingTag - Billing Tag is an optional free-form tag which is used for grouping billing records together. If supplied, it must be between 4 - 16 characters, contain only alpha/numeric ASCII characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Grouping billing records by billing tag will be available in future releases.

    • getVolatileBlob

      public VolatileBlobApi.GetVolatileBlobAdapter getVolatileBlob(String hrn, String layerId, String dataHandle, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Retrieves a volatile data blob from storage.

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/data/{dataHandle}

      Method: GET

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : Array[Byte] (OK - Response includes a blob)

      code 204 : (Blob is empty)

      code 401 : AuthenticationMessage (Unauthorized)

      code 403 : AuthorizationMessage (Forbidden)

      code 404 : (Not Found - no blob is associated with this dataHandle)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The ID of the parent layer for this volatile data blob.
      dataHandle - The data handle identifies a specific volatile data blob so that you can get that blob's contents.
      billingTag - Billing Tag is an optional free-form tag which is used for grouping billing records together. If supplied, it must be between 4 - 16 characters, contain only alpha/numeric ASCII characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Grouping billing records by billing tag will be available in future releases.

    • patchVolatileBlob

      public VolatileBlobApi.PatchVolatileBlobAdapter patchVolatileBlob(String hrn, String layerId, String dataHandle, com.here.platform.data.client.base.generated.scaladsl.model.data_volatile.PatchProperties patchProperties, Optional<String> xReplicate, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Modify ttl of the volatile data blob in the underlying storage mechanism (volume).

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/data/{dataHandle}

      Method: PATCH

      Expected answers:

      code 204 : (No Content - A new ttl was set)

      code 400 : (Bad Request)

      code 401 : AuthenticationMessage (Unauthorized)

      code 403 : AuthorizationMessage (Forbidden)

      code 404 : (Not Found)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The ID of the layer that the volatile data blob belongs to.
      dataHandle - The data handle (ID) represents an identifier for the volatile data blob.
      patchProperties - Modify ttl value of the blob
      xReplicate - If set to true, it indicates the request is a replication call. It is not required for user to set it manually
      billingTag - Billing Tag is an optional free-form tag which is used for grouping billing records together. If supplied, it must be between 4 - 16 characters, contain only alpha/numeric ASCII characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Grouping billing records by billing tag will be available in future releases.

    • putVolatileBlob

      public VolatileBlobApi.PutVolatileBlobAdapter putVolatileBlob(String hrn, String layerId, String dataHandle, byte[] body, Optional<String> xReplicate, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Persists the volatile data blob in the underlying storage mechanism (volume).

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/data/{dataHandle}

      Method: PUT

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : (OK - A new blob was uploaded)

      code 204 : (No Content - An existing blob was updated)

      code 400 : (Bad Request)

      code 401 : AuthenticationMessage (Unauthorized)

      code 403 : AuthorizationMessage (Forbidden)

      code 404 : (Not Found)

      code 507 : (Volatile layer out of space)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The ID of the layer that the volatile data blob belongs to.
      dataHandle - The data handle (ID) represents an identifier for the volatile data blob.
      body - The data to upload as part of the blob. Size limit: 2 MB
      xReplicate - If set to true, it indicates the request is a replication call. It is not required for user to set it manually
      billingTag - Billing Tag is an optional free-form tag which is used for grouping billing records together. If supplied, it must be between 4 - 16 characters, contain only alpha/numeric ASCII characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Grouping billing records by billing tag will be available in future releases.
